* Myfunction_2.java:
```Java
import com.microsoft.z3.*;
import java.util.HashMap;

public class Myfunction_2{
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        HashMap<String, String> m = new HashMap<String,String>();
        Context ctx = new Context(m);

        IntExpr a = ctx.mkIntConst("a");
        IntExpr b = ctx.mkIntConst("b");
        IntExpr c = ctx.mkIntConst("c");
        Optimize opt = ctx.mkOptimize();
      
        // let a + 2*b + 3*c = 22
        BoolExpr formula = ctx.mkEq(
            ctx.mkAdd(
                ctx.mkMul(a,ctx.mkInt(1)), 
                ctx.mkMul(b,ctx.mkInt(2)), 
                ctx.mkMul(c,ctx.mkInt(3))
                ),
            ctx.mkInt(22)
            );
        System.out.println("formula : " + formula);

        /* constraints definition */
        BoolExpr constraint_1 = ctx.mkGe(a, ctx.mkInt(0));  // a >= 0
        BoolExpr constraint_2 = ctx.mkLt(a, ctx.mkInt(10)); // a < 10
        BoolExpr constraint_3 = ctx.mkGe(b, ctx.mkInt(0));  // b >= 0
        BoolExpr constraint_4 = ctx.mkLt(b, ctx.mkInt(10)); // b < 10
        BoolExpr constraint_5 = ctx.mkGe(c, ctx.mkInt(0));  // c >= 0
        BoolExpr constraint_6 = ctx.mkLt(c, ctx.mkInt(10)); // c < 10
        
        /* add constraints into the optimizing solver */           
        opt.Add(
            formula,
            constraint_1,
            constraint_2,
            constraint_3,
            constraint_4,
            constraint_5,
            constraint_6
            );  
        
         /* the optimize goal */
        Optimize.Handle mc = opt.MkMaximize(c);
        
        if(opt.Check() == Status.SATISFIABLE)
        {
            Model model = opt.getModel();
            System.out.println("model : " + model);

            Expr ma = model.eval(a,false); 
            Expr mb = model.eval(b,false); 
  
            System.out.println("\nma = " + ma);
            System.out.println("\nmb = " + mb);   

            System.out.println("\nmc = " + mc);
            System.out.println("upperc = " + mc.getUpper());
            System.out.println("lowerc = " + mc.getLower());
        }else
        {
            System.out.println("not satisfiable");
        }   
    }
}
```

* The output of Myfunction_2.java:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41780406/43523313-8ec22be4-95ce-11e8-87a5-377d7a7e274a.png)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* The temporary solution for the Myfunction_1.java:
**<Solution 1>**.  Multiply each coefficient of the formula by 2 (e.g. 2*a + 4*b + 6*c = 44)
After a lot of tests, I found that if the coefficients of the formula are not equal to 1, then the result will be right. 
The output will be:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41780406/43523218-455c1d52-95ce-11e8-9101-c2c8d8f38d9c.png)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* The temporary solution for the Myfunction_2.java:
**<Solution 1>**. Same as the above solution, multiply each coefficient of the formula by 2 (e.g. 2*a + 4*b + 6*c = 44)
The output will be:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41780406/43525498-86e340e2-95d4-11e8-8210-a41a52aeeb89.png)

    **<Solution 2>**. Replace the mkLt with mkLe in constraint_2, constraint_4, and constraint_6. For example, replacing ctx.mkLt(a, ctx.mkInt(10)) with ctx.mkLe(a, ctx.mkInt(9)).
The output will be:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41780406/43524369-b0371d40-95d1-11e8-930d-ecfab6a142ad.png)

    It would be kind of tricky because both of solutions don't change the meaning of constraints. However, the right answer can be got from Z3.

* Conclusion
1. We should avoid any coefficient of the formula is equal to 1.
2. If any coefficient of the formula is equal to 1, we should use mkLe instead of mkLt, or the result in the model would be wrong. Moreover, we should get the result in the model and recompute the optimize goal for verifying.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
My Z3 version is 4.8.0.0. 
In addition, it is possible that there are same bugs in #1326. Note that the coefficients of the formula in #1326 are equal to 1.
If you are interested in this issue, you are welcome to share your ideas. Thanks!

